President Barack Obama announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Holy See to attend the Canonization Mass of Father Damien on October 11, 2009. The delegation will be led by U.S. Ambassador to the Holy See, Miguel Humberto Diaz. Other members of the delegation include U.S. Senator Daniel Kahikina Akaka, U.S. Congressman Donald M. Payne, Superintendent of Kalaupapa National Historic Park Stephen Prokop, Bishop of Honolulu Larry Silva, and President of the Catholic Health Association of the United States Sister Carol Ann Keehan.